# üêû bug report

### Affected Package
@angular/animation


### Is this a regression?

No


### Description

Initially there's an array of objects for *ngFor display in HTML, and each object is assigned a boolean property "show" with value false in OnInit( ). And "show" is used to indicate the animation state 'initial' or 'final' that is defined in component.

The animation 'trigger' works fine at the beginning, but after changing the order of the objects in the array (sort or reverse), Angular Animation seems to lose binding to the objects, and the 'trigger' doesn't do anything when trying to trigger the first time, but it works fine on the second time and so on.

Expected behaviour: after changing order of the objects (sort / reverse), the animation should work at the first 'trigger'.

Please check the stackblitz below.


## üî¨ Minimal Reproduction

https://stackblitz.com/edit/angular-ivy-ehgtbm


